    Overview

    This is a NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) quiz preparation application that allows students to create subjects, chapters, and quizzes. The app can scrape quiz content from Gemini URLs or accept PDF uploads to automatically generate multiple-choice questions. It features a timed quiz interface with progress tracking, performance analytics, and results visualization.

    User Preferences

    Preferred communication style: Simple, everyday language.

    System Architecture

    Frontend Architecture

    • Framework: React with TypeScript using Vite as the build tool
    • Routing: Wouter for client-side routing with pages for dashboard, subjects, quizzes, and results
    • State Management: React Context API for global app state (quiz sessions, navigation) combined with TanStack Query for server state
    • UI Framework: Shadcn/ui components built on Radix UI primitives with Tailwind CSS for styling
    • Form Handling: React Hook Form with Zod validation for type-safe form management

    Backend Architecture

    • Runtime: Node.js with Express.js server
    • Language: TypeScript with ES modules
    • Database ORM: Drizzle ORM with PostgreSQL as the database
    • File Storage: JSON file-based storage system (MemStorage class) for development/testing
    • API Design: RESTful API with structured error handling and request logging middleware

    Data Storage Solutions

    • Primary Database: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM for schema management and migrations
    • Development Storage: JSON file-based storage (quiz-data.json) for local development
    • Schema: Well-defined database schema with subjects, chapters, slides, questions, and quiz attempts
    • Client Storage: LocalStorage for quiz progress persistence and user preferences

    Authentication and Authorization

    • Current State: No authentication system implemented
    • Session Management: Basic session handling with connect-pg-simple for PostgreSQL session storage
    • Security: CORS and basic Express security middleware

    External Dependencies

    Third-party Services

    • Google Gemini AI: Content scraping service (@google/genai) for generating quiz questions from Gemini URLs
    • Cheerio: HTML parsing library for web scraping functionality
    • Neon Database: Serverless PostgreSQL database provider (@neondatabase/serverless)

    Key Frontend Libraries

    • TanStack Query: Server state management and caching
    • Wouter: Lightweight client-side routing
    • Radix UI: Accessible component primitives for complex UI components
    • Tailwind CSS: Utility-first CSS framework for styling
    • React Hook Form: Form state management with validation

    Development Tools

    • Vite: Fast build tool and development server
    • TypeScript: Type safety across the entire application
    • Drizzle Kit: Database schema management and migrations
    • ESBuild: Fast JavaScript bundler for production builds

    Content Processing

    • PDF Processing: Planned support for PDF content extraction (referenced in schema but not fully implemented)
    • Web Scraping: Automated question generation from web content using Cheerio and Puppeteer fallback
